				<td colspan="2"><span>The Reed's spreadsheet scared me a couple times cause it looked complex to me.  Twice I loaded it up and went OMG.  However, the third time I said I was going to force myself to figure it out.  After all, by 32 years of age I should be able to read a spreadsheet!  
<br />

<br />
I am SO glad I took a 3rd look at it.  It is very useful.  If you're hesitant like I was, all I can say is persevere.  It's well worth the time to figure out how it works.  
<br />

<br />
And welcome to barding.  You'll run into some bad bards out there just like any other class but the vast majority of bards I've met were all very helpful and understanding.  What I've started to find particularly satisfying is when someone you've grouped with before, recommends you to other people.  Last night I got my first group invite from a stranger for a plane of justice group. It was a good feeling. I promptly went and twisted 4 songs for the group while doing CC and had a blast.  
<br />

<br />
Rock on fellow bard!  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
