				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Hello Im New<a name="24128"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 26 04 2:46 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I know there are many others on this board that could answer your question better than I, but here is what I do.....
<br />

<br />
I make a social macro for each of my 8 song slots.  I put those social macros on my hotkeys.  That way to play song 1 I just hit the corresponding macro key.  My macros are simple since I only put one song per macro.  I tried putting 2 songs per macro but a missed not really messed me up. 
<br />

<br />
Macro looks like this:
<br />

<br />
/stopsong
<br />
/cast 1
<br />

<br />
That's it.  By pressing 1, it stops whatever I was singing and casts the song in gem slot #1.  I do the same for the other 7 slots.  
<br />

<br />
To twist I then just hit 1....wait for song to finish casting.....hit 2.....wait....hit 3......wait......and hit 4.  Then repeat.  It takes no mouse clicks at all.  Try that and see if it helps you out.  I twist for a few hours at a time with no pain or difficulties.  Hope it helps!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Impresario Bardtail Mathers <br>
Lvl 65 Maestro of Stromm <br>
Prime Syndicate</span></td>
